hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: Looking for work inboxfitness.com I know Hunnam is a good actor but his performance in “Pacific Rim” is one of the most awkward and uncomfortable I’ve seen in a long time.  When a talented actor is made to look otherwise in performance, it’s usually the director’s fault.  You have no idea how much I hate picking on Guillermo del Toro, but since I’m going to give him credit for everything that’s good about “Pacific Rim,” I’m going to blame him for everything that’s bad — and in my opinion, there’s more bad than good.
